    "title": "Databse error / fatal error on ecternal encrypted HDD",
    "body": "I have got some major errors as well on v.0.11.0 as on v0.12.1.\n\nI use a truecrypt encrypted external HDD where the whole wallet and blockchain is stored. \nI start it with \"W:\\Mining_Bitcoin_\\Bitcoin\\bitcoin-qt.exe -datadir=W:\\Mining_Bitcoin_\\Bitcoin\"\n\nThis is the way I used to do since years and it always worked fine that way (same external HDD, same encryption).\n\nSince some month I get major errors escpeially database errors. \nI reindexed several times but got the same problem right afetr it again.\n\nFor more info and some debug logs see here: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1454836.new#new\n",
